Apple's older EFI firmware (tested on a MacPro5,1) hangs when the EFI partition's
grub.cfg calls configfile at top level during early startup.

Rendering some output first avoids it, so we just present a loading transition.

--- /usr/lib/live/build/binary_grub-efi	2026-07-19 12:00:00.000000000 +0100
+++ /usr/lib/live/build/binary_grub-efi	2026-07-19 12:00:00.000000000 +0100
@@ -230,6 +230,9 @@
 # config from that same partition.
 mkdir -p ${_CHROOT_DIR}/grub-efi-temp-cfg
 cat >${_CHROOT_DIR}/grub-efi-temp-cfg/grub.cfg <<EOF
+terminal_output console
+echo "Loading FyshOS..."
+sleep 1
 search --set=root --file /.disk/info
 set prefix=(\\\$root)/boot/grub
 configfile (\\\$root)/boot/grub/grub.cfg
